Catalpa Ave., south side, between 62nd Street (left) and Fresh Pond Road (right), showing the Philip Edsall house. At the right foreground are circus tents. View No. 2 shows an outbuilding facing 62nd Street and in the background brick tenements on the west side of Fresh Pond Road. In No. 3 is another view of the outbuilding, once the Ivanhoe Volunteer Company's Pumping Station built by Hy. W. Mayer in 1890 at his expense. None of these buildings appear in 1929.

1922.
Views 1 & 3.
View 2: March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
